Optional a_im

a_im: string

Indicates a change feed request. Must be set to "Incremental feed", or omitted otherwise.

Optional disableRUPerMinuteUsage

disableRUPerMinuteUsage: boolean
  • Defined in src/request/FeedOptions.ts:13

DisableRUPerMinuteUsage is used to enable/disable Request Units(RUs)/minute capacity to serve the request if regular provisioned RUs/second is exhausted.

Optional enableCrossPartitionQuery

enableCrossPartitionQuery: boolean
  • Defined in src/request/FeedOptions.ts:19

A value indicating whether users are enabled to send more than one request to execute the query in the Azure Cosmos DB database service.

More than one request is necessary if the query is not scoped to single partition key value.

Optional enableScanInQuery

enableScanInQuery: boolean
  • Defined in src/request/FeedOptions.ts:21

Allow scan on the queries which couldn't be served as indexing was opted out on the requested paths.

Optional initialHeaders

initialHeaders: IHeaders
  • Defined in src/request/FeedOptions.ts:35

(Advanced use case) Initial headers to start with when sending requests to Cosmos

Optional maxDegreeOfParallelism

maxDegreeOfParallelism: number
  • Defined in src/request/FeedOptions.ts:27

The maximum number of concurrent operations that run client side during parallel query execution in the Azure Cosmos DB database service. Negative values make the system automatically decides the number of concurrent operations to run.

Optional maxItemCount

maxItemCount: number
  • Defined in src/request/FeedOptions.ts:29

Max number of items to be returned in the enumeration operation.

Optional partitionKey

partitionKey: string
  • Defined in src/request/FeedOptions.ts:31

Specifies a partition key definition for a particular path in the Azure Cosmos DB database service.

Optional populateQueryMetrics

populateQueryMetrics: boolean
  • Defined in src/request/FeedOptions.ts:46

Enable returning query metrics in response headers

Optional sessionToken
